Telecom Italia Announces 2.6% Fixed-Line Monthly Fee Increase

-- B y   C h i a r a   R e m o n d i n i
-- 
2011-04-16T12:29:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-16/telecom-italia-announces-2-6-fixed-line-monthly-fee-increase.html
Telecom Italia SpA (TIT) ,  Italy â€™s biggest
phone company, will increase its fixed-line monthly fee by 2.6
percent, according to an advertisement published in newspapers
including  la Repubblica  today.  The monthly fee will advance to 16.5 euros ($23.81)
compared with 16.08 euros, from July 1, according to the
advertisement. The phone company will also apply new rates,
removing peak and off-peak tariffs, for local and long-distance
calls, charging 0.7 cents and 5 cents a minute, respectively, it
said.  Telecom Italia said the connection charge will remain
unchanged at 7.87 cents.  To contact the reporter on this story:
